PROJECTION
find() takes a second argument to choose which fields to return. 1 includes a field, 0 excludes it. You can't mix include and exclude, except _id which is always allowed since it's included by default.
db.customers.find({}, { name: 1, city: 1 })
db.customers.find({}, { email: 0 })

SORT, LIMIT, SKIP
sort() orders results — 1 for ascending, -1 for descending. Fast if the field has an index, slower otherwise since MongoDB sorts in memory.
limit() returns only a set number of results. skip() skips a number of documents from the start, usually combined with limit() for pagination.
skip() gets slow on very large page numbers because MongoDB still has to go through the skipped documents internally, even without returning them.